title: For Sale:  Glock 19 rtf2 with gills- Hard to find
postcontent:
NO TRADES FOR HANGUNS!!!!  This is a very hard to find Glock 19 rtf2 with gills.  It is a Gen 3, some say Gen 3.5 because it was ran at the end of the Gen 3's.  The rtf2 is an aggressive grip and the serrations were changed to experiment with better grip for cocking the firearm. Due to diehard fans not liking the changes Glock discontinued these firearms. You can no longer get the gilled serrations and only law enforcement is offered the rtf2(rough textured frame) grip. People list the rtf2 guns as rare which is semi accurate however NOT ALL ARE RARE. The most rare rtf2 are the 23c rtf2 with gills and 22c with gills. Then the 19 rtf2 with gills.  This is due to shorter production runs. The 22 and 17 rtf2 are readily available everywhere.  You can not find these on here or gunbroker very often. Here is what the last one on gunbroker sold for. See the link below. With transfer and shipping tbey are almost 900.
This gun will come with all the original Glock stuff; case, paperwork, stock sights, two mags.I also have a factory glock 33rd extended magazine and truglo tfo sights on it. I will also throw in 100 rounds of 9mm winchester white box ammo. This thing as about 100 rounds down the pipe but is in like new condition.  Never been holstered and sits in my safe. I will sell everything for $800 or 750 for everything minus the extended mag and truglo sights. Do your research before you email me or give me your opinion about this gun. Those who know Glocks know what this is. I will also consider a trade towards a Tavor that I will throw cash into as well. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  1932 Izhevsk hex receiver Mosin Nagant. /25\ re-arsenal stamp
postcontent:
Here is an excellent condition 1932 Izhevsk Mosin Nagant rifle. This rifle has a hex shaped receiver with near perfect bluing on the entire rifle. The stock is also in excellent condition and has the less common brass end pieces on the upper hand guard.

This rifle was was refurbished by the Soviets at the /25\ (Triangle-25) facility, which is known for painting the sight numbers in a red paint. They were the only facility known to have done this and the reason behind it is unknown, though it does add some interesting character to the rifles. I've owned three from /25\ and they've all been fantastic shooters, this one included. The bolt fit is nice and tight and this one has done 2" groups at 100 yards using standard Russian surplus 148gr rounds.

Sales only to Washington residents, must show drivers license and sign a bill of sale stating your legally allowed to purchase and own a firearm.
